parameters:
The voice has been turned OFF. If you want to turn it back
ON, you can do so from the same place.
\n<Eury>I'm tired... Maybe I should take a little break.

\n<Eury>The public order in this city might be worse than I thought.
I have to be careful...

\n<Eury>Today I fought monsters and started my first solo mission,
I'm really tired...

\n<Eury>Monsters are more active at night, so maybe I should really
go on a monster hunt...
\n<Eury>Maybe today I should prioritize getting some rest!

\n<Eury>Is there a service here that helps you recover from fatigue,
like a massage or something?

\n<Eury>...I had another rough day today. What does everyone think a
modified girl is?

\n<Eury>What should I do tonight? Maybe it's time to go on a monster
hunt...?

During nighttime, you can participate in night-exclusive
events like massages.
Also, you can go on monster hunts from the town's entrance.

If you don't have anything particular to do, you can sleep
in bed to skip time.

\n<Eury>Ugh... That was the first time something like that happened
to me...
\n<Eury>What should I do with my night?

\n<Eury>This city is full of perverts... I wonder if Makina-senpai
had it this tough too?

\n<Eury>It's been five days since I came to this city. It feels like
I've been harassed non-stop...

\n<Eury>My mission isn't just about hunting monsters. I'm starting
to worry if I can really fulfill it...

...Eury got into bed and some time passed, with the clock
soon to strike midnight.

It's the end of Eury's fifth day in this city. This moment
could be a turning point in her fate...!
\n<Eury>A fluffy bed. But now's not the time to rest!

In the Virgin Chapter, you cannot skip time by resting. In
the Non-Virgin Chapter, you can rest until nighttime.
Shall we rest until the evening?
\n<Eury>What shall I do to pass the time tonight?
\n<Eury>Was there a service that could help relieve fatigue?
Shall we rest until tomorrow morning?
Shall we rest until tomorrow morning?
Shall we rest until tomorrow morning?
Shall we rest until tomorrow morning?

\n<Eury>It's the \v[224]th day since we've come to Tengen Street.
Let's do our best today too!
\n<Eury>I don't have the energy to go outside anymore today...

\n<Eury>There are so many different types of monsters... I need to
gather information bit by bit to make fighting them easier.

\n<Monster Maniac>The scent of blood from slaying monsters...! You're a
modified girl, aren't you?

\n<Monster Maniac>My name is \C[24]Monster Maniac\C[0]. I love monsters more
than three meals a day.

\n<Monster Maniac>Their diversity, ferocity, and even their adorableness. The
majestic charm that pets can't cross over!

\n<Monster Maniac>\C[2]I live next door, so show me your Monster
Encyclopedia!!
\n<Eury>Eh...! There's such a suspicious person living next door!?
\n<Monster Maniac>It's a promise then. See you.
\n<Monster Maniac>I'll be waiting in the room next door!
\n<Eury>To think there are people who like monsters...

\n<Eury>I'm not keen on it... but he didn't seem like a bad person,
so maybe I'll go see him?

The Monster Maniac lives in the room next door. If you
collect the Monster Encyclopedia and talk to him, something
good might happen?

\n<Makina>Eury, it's been a week since the mission started. How's
everything going in Tengen Street?

\n<Eury>Makina-senpai!! Yay-! I'm so happy to receive a transmission
from you!

\n<Eury>Yes, the mission is going well! ...or at least, that's what
I'd like to say, but, well...
\n<Makina>It seems like there's something on your mind.
\n<Eury>Actually... I've been feeling a bit less confident lately.
\n<Makina>I see... Is there a clear reason?

\n<Eury>Well, I've been able to help around the town, but people
don't listen to me or they're mean to me. Maybe they're
looking down on me because I'm new...

\n<Makina>The place has always had poor security. There must be many
people there who are unlike those you're used to seeing from
where you grew up.

\n<Eury>Maybe I can't hide my ojou-sama aura? Plus, I am a savior's
modified girl after all!!

\n<Makina>Heh. The way you try to stay positive and motivate yourself
is one of your strengths, Eury.
\n<Eury>Well... But I still feel like I have a long way to go...

\n<Makina>No one gets everything right from the start. This mission is
a first for you, Eury.

\n<Makina>I believe that you can complete the mission. I feel that you
have the qualities of a hero, Eury.

\n<Makina>Marion also made that judgment, which is why she decided on
this solo mission for you.

\n<Eury>I feel like somehow everything will work out! Thank you,
Makina-senpai!

\n<Makina>Ah, yes. It's good that you've regained your confidence, but
there's one last thing I want to remind you of.
\n<Eury>That's right!! After all, I am a modified girl!!

\n<Makina>The most important thing to be careful of is not monsters,
but human malice. Tengen Street has bad security.

\n<Makina>Be careful not to be targeted by people with ill
intentions...
\n<Makina>Wait a minute! Are you even listening to what I'm saying?!?

\n<Eury>Then, I'll get back to my mission! You do your best too,
Makina-senpai! Bye!!!
\n<Eury>Alright! I'll do my best to live up to expectations!!
